What really raised suspicion is that the install guy just so happened to “be in the area” and was able to come  and “install right away.” Most places, you have to schedule right? I truly believe that the install guy was probably following the salesman around waiting on a sale.
During the time of the installation,  I decided to research the company. I know that you’ll see good/ bad reviews with most companies but Vivint was HORRIBLE!! Aside from checking the reviews on their Facebook page,  they had bad reviews with BBB, Yelp,  Rip off report, and even 20/20 launched an investigation on the company!!!!
At this point it was 9 at night,  we had the install guy stop everything and come back the next day.  I immediately called to cancel our “3 day trial” in which I’m hoping we’ll get our money refunded to us..contrary to what the reviews state. Thankfully we got out before we were locked into this nightmare of a company.
Please train your salespeople to properly and honestly explained the contract and other perks. Also please please have them to stop using scare tactics in order to make sales.  It’s not good for a business.
