User Score
1



Todd Dreeszen


				July 24th, 2017				Ocala, FL

4 people found this review helpful!
On the 14th of June 2017 I made a call to Vivint inquiring about a camera security system. The representative gathered information about reasoning for needing security cameras. After recommending their system I began gathering information about their products. He stated that I would likely need 3 cameras that he said were 1080p HD with night vision (the top of the line they offered)  and covered around 165 degrees each. One camera for the front, one camera for the back and one dedicated to our “problem” area. This area was a renter who had pointed a gun at me the previous day and when the police showed I had no witness’s or video.  So he informed me that it was going to be a 6yr contract and he needed to charge my debit card that night for around $53 to cover the installation No problem right, after all you want your life and family protected for longer than 6 years right.
    So on the morning of the 15th the tech shows up to install. I go over where I would like the cameras installed with the tech and asked for his recommendation as well, since he does do this for a living. At this time he informs me there is going to be significant gaps in video coverage. I’m confused so I ask to explain to me these gaps, he tells me that since the cameras only cover about 45 to 50 degrees each I’m going to have a lot of dead space. Woah…. strike # 1!!! I ask him to get his manager on the phone now. Oh BTW we have been with ADT for 13 years before the 15th of June and cancelled on the 15th (Vivint offered financing and ADT didn’t) So we are in a bit of a pickle, no security active at this point, the tech’s manager authorized an additional “doorbell camera” to be added to cover some of the dead space. Doorbell camera covers about 160 degrees with a fishbowl appearance through the camera.
      Five hours later the three outdoor cameras and the doorbell camera are installed and activated. Couldn’t get worse right? While I’m e-signing the contract I read the satisfaction policy, it states that I have 3 days to evaluate the system and if for any reason I’m not happy call for a refund and the contract will be null and void. Heck no! I said you better get your manager on the phone and give me a 30 day return policy or you can start taking your equipment down from my house. Manager says “I’ll go ahead an annotate it here in the record that I authorized a 30 day return policy.” NOT HAPPENING I said you send me an email right now or I’m not signing a thing more. Well 5 minutes later I have an email extending my return (It’s called and ROR) for 30 days. Use that term and people will listen when they are installing or trying to sell you something.
     Note to the buyer, you better have the best (fastest) WiFi available or you will be me as well. I have COX which has the fastest speed available 300meg down 30meg up. This system NEEDS UPLOAD SPEED! Every camera requires a MINIMUM of 1.5meg UPLOAD speed. All cameras are wireless,  hardwired for power and WiFi for data transmission. The very first night we had issues with the cameras dropping off line without us knowing about it. We had to call the next day and set an appointment for them to come back out to try and fix the brand new system out of the box! 4 days later the same tech comes out and puts in a single signal booster in attempt to attain the required signal strength (80% BTW) this is found on your 7in LCD control panel.
    The tech was unable to get the necessary signal strength after multiple attempts that afternoon. BTW we have a 4 bedroom 2 bath single story regular pitch house, nothing crazy. So the tech said he doesn’t  know what to do he has done everything he can. So we had to call back to set another appointment up, two days later on the next appointment time 8-11AM the tech doesn’t show doesn’t call nothing. I have to call them. Now they tell me it’s going to be another 4 days before they can get the next tech out! During this time we evaluate our coverage’s and conclude we will need another 2 cameras to cover the dead spots (someone was able to get under one of our cameras and have a cigarette and blow smoke to the camera during night vision). The next tech shows up assess the situation installs 2 more cameras and another booster and the system appears to be working with all cameras above the required 80%. Yeah…right?
     We had multiple cameras go offline over the week end without us knowing. The system comes with video clips that it stores when the cameras detects motion within the areas you set up. Well we would have no footage for hours at a time during the night and day. So we had to set up another appointment and guess what happened they no called no showed us again. I was talking to them on one line and my wife was calling them to cancel on the other line!! We agreed to have one more person come out and try to fix it. He arrived and attempted to fix it by changing out the control panel as well as remove their wireless router that was running thru our wireless router (made no sense) and was successful in attaining 3.8meg upload speed from the control panel. At this point we initiated the cancellation with the service tech while he was on speaker phone with the RoR department manager (Make sure you do this) so the manager can send an email to me validating the cancellation was received and the appointment was made by them to come get the equipment and no further action was required by myself other to be at my house for them to come pick up the equipment. When the date came for the appointment to pick up their equipment they didn’t show, I called them at 11:05 and told them they didn’t show and the equipment was mine I had a phone call 15 later by a tech that said “I was in the neighborhood and wasn’t supposed to be there till tomorrow but I can be there in 15 minutes”.
     Conclusion – System’s concept is awesome!! Cameras when they worked were very good, night vision was ok but still rate them good. Function was good except the system can’t be viewed on “playback” (your reviewing continues footage from the previous time period of your choice) from anything but your mobile device. Doorbell camera was great in quality and function (only one that never lost connection). To this day I’m still waiting for our refund, the absolute worst customer service by virtue of the division of labor. No one department can help you with the other. When you are transferred in starts you in the Q for another department. My average was 1hr 17mins every time I called, with my longest being 2:14 while trouble shooting the system. If you have no problem dealing with this for 6 yrs or you can drop over $1700 upfront and incur a 3 yr contract and own cameras that drop off line every day multiple times go for it. I do wish I had this review before I even tried the system out.
Was this review helpful? Yes

